<a href="https://www.natyasutraonline.com/picture-gallery/asamyuta-hasta-bharatanatyam/Candrakala-Hasta/#:~:text=Release%20of%20thumb%20from%20Suchi,river%20and%20Club%20(weapon).">Chandrakalaa Mudra</a> is the fourteenth of the 28 single hand mudras (Asamyutta Hasta) detailed in the <em>Abhinaya Darpana</em>. The term "Chandrakalaa" translates to "Digit of the Moon." This mudra involves releasing the thumb into the Suchi Mudra position, allowing it to remain straight, resembling the Shikhara gesture.

